(169, 1, '2019-05-30 18:47:24', '2019-05-30 17:47:24', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":160} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/1280px-CGI_logo.svg_-1-1024x480.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-160\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have always been fascinated by the special effects\nused in hollywood movies and I have always wanted to be able to create the same\nthings my self. Unfortunately, we didnt learn much about this during our video\nediting classes, thats why I chose to write a paper on CGI. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now a days special effects are an integral part of the\nmotion pictures and TV  Series. From shows like Game of Thrones to epic\nblockbusters like the Marvels Avengers Endgame, special effects are one of the\nmain reasons why these films and shows are so popular. With the help of these\nspecial effects, film makers are able to create scenes and effects which may\nnot be feasible using other methods. These special effects often use a technique\ncalled CGI, Computer Generated Imagery. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In 1972, the co-founder of Pixar, Edwin Catmull, pioneered\nthe first 3D computer animation. He created a computer generated hand by first\ncreating a mold of his own hand using plaster. He then drew a few hundred\ntriangles and shapes on hand model, meassured the length and coordinates of\nthese shapes, and entered them in to a 3D animation program to generate the CG\nhand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But the first realistic CGI portrayal of human\nmovement and facial features is arguable, though movies like Terminator 2:\nJudgment Day and Fight Club are notable pioneers in CGI acting and facial\nalteration technology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CGI has become very popular over the past two decades,\nand their importance and use will increase even further in the future because\nof their wide applicability in various fields. And as we create more advanced\ntechnology, the quality and realism of the images and effects created through\nCGI will become even more realistic aswell. But before we go any further, let\nme explain what CGI is and how it works. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What is CGI?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CGI stands for Computer-generated imagery, most\ncommonly refers to 3D computer generated graphics used to creating scenes and\nspecial effects in both live-action / animated films and television series. From\n2D copmuter imagery all the way to the computer generated feature films, CGI\nhas to be one of the most noteworthy technological changes in screen history\nallowing directors and producers to leap into a new bold limitless world. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>How does it\nwork?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Designers create a series of computer-generated\ngraphics. After the basic graphics are created, the next step is to bring them\nto life. To make the graphics look real, creators pay special attention to\ndetails such as texture, lighting, and color. These details are what makes\nanimation look real and not cartoonish. In live-action films the graphics are\nmixed into the previously filmed scenes. This makes lighting very important.\nThe lighting on the graphics must match the lighting from the scene in order\nfor the finished product to be seamless. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>CGI requires the rendering of a 3D model of a scene,\nobject, or person in a computer. Usually designers make a 3D model first and\nthen start working on the textures and the colors of the object and after the\nfirst draft is made, the CG artist can alter the model and translate it into\nthe final product. There are different types of CGI and visual effects that are\nused for different types of situations and purposes. And here I am going to\ndiscuss f types of them.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1)\nAdding background scenery and visual effects on a green screen: </strong>This is one of the most\ncommon visual effects that the filmmakers use and green screens can be found in\nalmost every film set. But why the color green you ask? Well it\'s because it\ndoesn\'t match any natural skin tone or hair color, meaning no part of an actor\nwill be edited out through chroma key. In the following image you can see\nhow the designers added stunning scenery in a scene behind the actors with the\nhelp of the visual effects and a green screen. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":162} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/a.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-162\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2)\nMotion Capture: </strong>Motion capture is the process of recording the movement of objects\nor people, especially the recording of an actor\'s movements and facial\nexpressions for the purpose of animating a digital character in a film. It is\nusually used in superhero movies to digitally create the characters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":163} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/fzf.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-163\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>\nAvatar</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3)\nDummy Actors: </strong>For films where the acting of a special actor is not needed\n(usually happens when the creature is animated or digitally created),\nfilmmakers use dummy actors. They are not really actors, but they are just\nthere to help the actors perform good in the scenes. Since the characters are\ndigitally animated later, actors sometimes have difficulty doing scenes with\nsomething that doesn\'t exist, and dummy actors effect helps them with that.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":164} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dqsdqd.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-164\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><br>\nMarvels Guardians of the Galaxy</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>4)De\naging technology: </strong>Filmmakers use the de aging effects on actors to show their\nyounger versions. Usually for the story purposes, for example if there is a\nflashback of an old character when they were young, filmmakers use the de aging\neffect. They try to replicate how the actors looked when they were young. It is\nboth amazing and horrifying to look at at the same time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":165} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dzqdqdq.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-165\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But computer\ngenerated imagery is not only used in film and tv shows. It is also used for\neducation, science and visualization and for product design and engeniering. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Scientific Visualization: </strong>In science this technology is used to\nvisualise the data collected from various tests and experiments. For example,\nvisualising how atoms of a material react in specific conditions.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":166} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dazdsdqsd-1024x448.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-166\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Education: </strong>The scientific data can be visualised using CGI to\nmake it easier for students to understand. For example, visualisation of our\nsolar system for astronomy students.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":167} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/qsdqsdsqd.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-167\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Product Design and Engineering: </strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Designers and\nengineers use special CAD (computer aided design) software for designing,\ndeveloping and manufacturing consumer and industrial products. This is mostly\nused in architecture. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":168} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/dqzdq.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-168\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I am satisfied\nwith this research and I am actually kind of surprised to see that there\ndifferent kinds of CGIs that are used for different things in different fields.\nI will use the information that I learned through writing this paper on a video\nproject I am working on with my friends.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'CGI', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '50-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-05-30 18:47:24', '2019-05-30 17:47:24', '', 50, 'http://portfolio.1819.zia.nxtmediatech.eu/2019/05/30/50-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
